Keji lakes core diatom counts

Source: R/data.R
keji_lakes.Rd

A subset of well-labeled, clean diatom count data for 3 Keji-area (Nova Scotia) lakes, which form part of the analysis in Ginn et al. (2007). These data are in the form of a mudata object, from which location information, parameter information, and data can be extracted using tbl_locations, tbl_params, and tbl_data (respectively). Also, a subset of these data amenable to plotting have been made available.

keji_lakes

keji_lakes_plottable

Format

An object of class mudata (inherits from list) of length 5.

Source

Neotoma paleoecology database (http://neotomadb.org/)

References

Ginn, Brian K., Brian F. Cumming, and John P. Smol. "Long-Term Lake Acidification Trends in High- and Low-Sulphate Deposition Regions from Nova Scotia, Canada." Hydrobiologia 586, no. 1 (July 1, 2007): 261-75. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-007-0644-3.

Examples

library(mudata2)
data(keji_lakes)

keji_lakes %>%
  tbl_data()
